# Environment Variables for Cloudinary Configuration
# IMPORTANT: Add this file to .gitignore to keep credentials secure

# Cloudinary Configuration
# Get these from your Cloudinary Dashboard: https://cloudinary.com/console
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=CLOUDINARY_API_KEY
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET
CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=your_upload_preset_here

# ⚠️ SECURITY WARNING: API_SECRET should NEVER be used in client-side code!
# The API_SECRET above should only be used for server-side operations
# For client uploads, use CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET instead

# Upload Preset Configuration Instructions:
# 1. Go to Settings > Upload in your Cloudinary Dashboard
# 2. Create a new Upload Preset with these settings:
#    - Mode: Unsigned (for client-side uploads)
#    - Folder: jenga_solutions (optional)
#    - Format: Auto
#    - Quality: Auto
#    - Resource type: Image
#    - Access control: Upload
#    - Maximum file size: 5MB
#    - Allowed formats: jpg, png, webp, jpeg
# 3. Copy the preset name and paste it above

# Security Notes:
# - Never commit API secrets to version control
# - Use unsigned upload presets for client uploads
# - Configure folder restrictions in Cloudinary dashboard
# - Set up proper access controls and rate limiting
#
# ⚠️ SECURITY WARNING:
# - CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET is included but should ONLY be used server-side
# - For client-side uploads, use CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET instead
# - API secrets in client code pose security risks
# - Consider rotating the API secret if it was previously exposed
